OL,7,FNew offences introduced to criminalise
OL,8,Fcyberflashing and epilepsy-trolling
OL,9,Fare among those taking effect on
OL,10,FWednesday, with online abusers now
OL,11,Ffacing prosecution for such acts.
OL,13,FThe new offences have come into effect
OL,14,Fas part of the Online Safety Act,
OL,15,Fwhich gained Royal Assent late last
OL,16,Fyear, and means criminals face up to
OL,17,Ffive years in prison for engaging in a
OL,18,Frange of online abuse, trolling and
OL,19,Fpredatory behaviour.
