OL,4,Ccriminalised and punishable under new
OL,5,Claws
OL,7,FUnder the new offences, abusers and ex-
OL,8,Fpartners who share, or threaten to
OL,9,Fshare, intimate images on or offline
OL,10,Fwithout consent will face up to six
OL,11,Fmonths in prison for the base offence
OL,12,Fof sharing such an image, rising to
OL,13,Ftwo years if it is proven the
OL,14,Fperpetrator also intended to cause
OL,15,Fdistress, alarm or humiliation, or to
OL,16,Fobtain sexual gratification.
OL,18,FCyberflashing perpetrators will face
OL,19,Fup to two years in prison where
OL,20,Fsimilar intent is also proven.
