OL,7,FThe government said this offence would
OL,8,Fbolster its commitment to clamping
OL,9,Fdown on dangerous disinformation and
OL,10,Fonline election interference.
OL,12,FIn addition, a further new offence
OL,13,Fwill mean that individuals who post
OL,14,Fcontent encouraging serious self-harm
OL,15,Fcould face up to five years in prison.
OL,17,FThe Crown Prosecution Service (CPS)
OL,18,Fhas also issued new guidance to
OL,19,Fprosecutors to coincide with the new
OL,20,Foffences taking effect.
